"'''Jade Solitaire'''" is a short story written by [[Timothy Zahn]] that appeared in the ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' anthology, which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]]. It takes place sometime before [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]] and is essentially the tale of how [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] acquires her formidable starship, the ''[[Jade's Fire]]'', which is seen in ''[[Star Wars: The Corellian Trilogy]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: The Hand of Thrawn Duology]]''. It also describes how the [[Togorian/Legends|Togorian]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[H'sishi/Legends|H'sishi]] came to join the crew of [[Talon Karrde]].

"Jade Solitaire" was originally scheduled to be published, alongside the accompanying ''[[Roleplaying Game Sourcefile]]'', in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 17|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' #17]], but the ''Adventure Journal'' ceased publication before it could be featured.

==Plot summary==
When wealthy industrialist [[Ja Bardrin]]'s daughter is captured by the [[Drach'nam]] [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Chay Praysh]], Bardrin comes to [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara]] seeking aid. To back up his demand, he takes the crew of Mara's ship hostage, warning that they will be [[Death/Legends|killed]] unless Mara rescues his daughter. He also instructs Mara that, if at all possible, Mara must also retrieve the [[Personal Luxury Yacht 3000/Legends|luxury yacht]] his daughter was traveling in when she was captured.

Mara allows herself to be captured by Praysh's pirate gang and feigns timidity to get herself thrown in with their pack of [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]], in the pirates' secret compound on [[Makksre]]. After a few [[Standard day/Legends|days]] of menial laboring, she finds and befriends Bardrin's daughter, [[Sansia Bardrin|Sansia]], as well as a [[Togorian/Legends|Togorian]] female named [[H'sishi/Legends|H'sishi]]. The three women develop a plan to escape and fight their way to the pirates' hangar, escaping in Sansia's captured [[Starship/Legends|ship]], the [[Jade's Fire|''Winning Gamble'']]. Just outside the [[Kvabja system/Legends|system]], the ''Gamble'' rendezvous with Bardrin's ship, which, to Mara's surprise, is now under the command of her employer, [[Talon Karrde]]. He explains that he became worried when Mara and her crew went missing, and quickly tracked them down and overpowered Bardrin and his thugs. 

Sansia berates her [[Parent/Legends|father]] for not coming to her rescue sooner, when Mara interjects that it's worse than that: Bardrin deliberately sent her to be captured by the pirates, since the ''Gamble'' has a highly advanced hidden sensor package, which recorded loads of valuable data about Praysh's base and various business dealings. Bardrin expected to retrieve the data when the ship (and incidentally) Sansia were returned to him. Furious, Sansia decides to make a gift of the ''Gamble'' to Mara. Bardrin is in no position to object, since otherwise Karrde is not in a mood to let him off the hook for threatening Mara and his crew. Alone with Karrde later, Mara announces that she wants to take a leave of absence from the organization and get some experience running her own business. Excited at the idea of having her own ship, free and clear, for the first time in her life, she re-christens it the ''Jade's Fire''.

==Continuity==
[[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara's]] independent trading company has folded by the time of the events of ''[[Specter of the Past]]''. Some characters describe it as having failed, while [[Talon Karrde|Karrde]] says that it was simply an experiment for Mara, and he always expected her to rejoin the organization.

